Do you guys think it would benefit to have some sort of kill count system for people in SB? For instance a two mercenaries come to a guild to help the guildleader in a war. He would be able to check how many successful kills they have had and in a sense, be able to see which of the two were the better killer. Another example could be if someone from a very respectable human guild was going out when no one was watching and killing human newbies. Well anyone could do the kill count system and check to see if hes killed anyone that the guild policies forbid him to do. Or something like that. Just a thought that it might be cool.   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>"If you make a man a fire, he will be warm for one night. However, if you set a man on fire, he will be warm for eternity."
